a-size-base: one out of three cats will eat these but that is the one who I needed to and these have helped him
a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2021
a-size-base 3: So the 2 year old healthy cat won't touch these, the five year old fat cat ate these once then wouldn't eat them again.  The 4 month old stray we adopted over a month ago who is having a hard time kicking a pretty bad kitty herpes flare loves these and he is the one who I needed these for.  We have been giving him 500mg lysine twice a day as the vet directed and keeping him on antibiotics to prevent a bacterial side infection in his lungs, but he has not been getting any better.  Within two days of giving him these he has less rattling in his lungs, this has been the only improvement in his condition we have seen in over a month.  I did the math and for 6 chews there is only about 70mg of lysine, and since we have been giving him high doses of lysine for over a month the lysine is obviously not the ingredient in these chews that is helping.  I am therefore left to assume it is the probiotic.  While he is still far from recovered this has given me hope and I am going to look into a more broad spectrum probiotic and see if we can get him over this flare and onto a preventive regime which I think these chews will make be a part of.

a-size-base: My Cat Thumbs His Nose At This
a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2021
a-size-base 3: Every cat is an individual, and they know what they like and what they don't. Although many cats seem to love these Biteables, my senior cat would have nothing to do with it. I tried a single treat whole, then broken in half, and he just sniffed it and walked away each time. The next morning I even broke one in half and hid it in the middle of his wet cat food, which he normally inhales the minute I put it in his bowl. He ate around the treat halves and left them in his otherwise empty bowl. He loves chicken, which is the primary ingredient in these treats, but apparently that wasn't enough to entice him. In people years my cat is 88 years old, so it's not like he's going to change his food preferences at this stage of his life. The "chicken and tuna recipe" on the package is a bit misleading, since the tuna is only "natural tuna flavor" and not the real deal, and the same with the "natural fish flavor." I am still rating this product 3 stars even though my cat didn't like it because I think the L-lysine, taurine, and probiotics probably would have been good for him if he had been willing to eat these treats.

a-size-base: Both of my cats hate the flavor
a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2021
a-size-base 3: Different cats have different tastes so normally I wouldn't give a product two stars just because my cats didn't like the flavor but I really think it's warranted and possibly even generous in the case of Get Naked Essential Health Biteables because both of my cats really love treats but they absolutely hate these.The package boasts that Get Naked Biteables provide essential health benefits including lysine and probiotics and that the #1 ingredient is real chicken--although that last one doesn't actually mean anything because they could be saying that the highest quality or most expensive ingredient is chicken, not necessarily that chicken makes up the largest actual portion.  In any case, these are not cat food--they are cat treats.  With cat food, strong health benefits are definitely something you want to look for but with treats the number one most important thing is flavor.  Cats should be thrilled when you pull out the package and they see that you are about to give them a treat.I have two cats.  They both love treats.  They both ate exactly one of these Get Naked Bitables treats and will not touch them again.  They absolutely hate the flavor which means these aren't much of a treat as far as my cats are concerned.  Get Naked Biteables might well be very nutritious but they neglected the single most important thing that every cat treat needs which is great taste.

a-size-base: A treat that is more like a vitamin!
a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on October 25, 2021
a-size-base 3: Our Siamese kitten is kind of picky about her food yet she loved these soft heart shaped chewable cat treats. They are made in the USA, and chicken is the first ingredient, however they smell more fishlike.  These treats are more than a treat, they are a probiotic containing Lysine which is an essential amino acid helps pets produce antibodies and enzymes that support immune systems.  It is also helpful for calcium absorption which supports strong bones and promotes healthy skin. This is important, so our kitties can fight diseases and have healthy bones. Cats do not make lysine on their own. They must obtain it through their food and supplements.  L-lysine is not for all cats so check with your vet. I do not agree on the dosage. I think these treats should be used sparingly because it can interfere with other medications. The package is small but affordable. I’m feeding our 7 month old cat one a day to support a healthy gut and immune system.

a-size-base: Combination of treat and treatment for my feline
a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2021
a-size-base 3: My older gray tabby has had feline herpesvirus since she was a young adult. Lysine can be a good thing to try to help these cats with their symptoms of sneezing and rasping. She loves these Biteables and seems to think they are a treat on par with Temptations, and that is in contrast to other lysine supplements she has quickly lost interest in.Cats with breathing difficulties sometimes also have trouble with their sense of smell, and I suspect the ingredients here such as natural fish and tuna flavors are strong enough (but pleasant to the human nose) to maintain their appeal to a congested kitty. The main ingredients here are chicken, glycerin, sweet potatoes, tapioca starch and L-lysine.These snacks also contains dried Bacillus fermentation product, designed to promulgate digestive health.The manufacturer recommends five to six of these soft treats per day. The treats are made in the US and specifics are not provided (that I can see) on where the ingredients are sourced.Review of Get Naked Essential Health Biteables, Land & Sea Recipe, 3 oz,Natural,912672

I got them for one elderly cat who's stool seemed to be a bit looser then normal on occasion and the vet could find no reason. I thought the probiotic aspect couldn't hurt and might help. I've been giving him the 5 per day as recommended but see no change other than the other cats resent me for not giving them as many, lol. It's only been about a week and a half and I'm running out so I'm not sure if my cat's issue is not probiotic related (probably) or I haven't been giving him these long enough or if that aspect of these is no good.But they all like them as treats so I'm happy.
